        <abstract> 
<p>Regret that the Archbishop of Canterbury and other English Bishops have severely censured <hi rend="italic">Essays and Reviews</hi> [1860]. Believe "such enquiries conducted in a spirit so earnest and reverential … must tend to elicit truth, and to foster a spirit of sound religion". [Signed by CD, numerous men of science, and others.]</p> 
